msItem.title:
How two women called Juliana and Barbara, went on a pilgrimage to Jerusalem, were attached by robbers who stole their provisions;
                      and how, when the thieves tried to eat them, the Virgin Mary turned the bread into stones upon which the thieves broke their teeth;
                      and how the thieves repented and restored twofold what they had stolen from the women, when the Virgin Mary had healed their wounded
                      mouths and mended their broken teeth

